----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Model defines structural and behavioral verification for REQ-SYS-01
-- Summary 2: Includes permission lattice, actor roles, resources, interfaces, and states
-- Summary 3: Covers acceptance criteria, edge cases, test cases, and NFR proxies
-- Summary 4: All assertions and runs are syntactically valid and consistent
-- Assumption 1: Permission lattice models a simple hierarchy (Read < Write < Execute < Admin)
-- Assumption 2: Resources have owners and accessible actors; owner is always accessible
-- Assumption 3: Interfaces have kind, encryption, and authentication flags
-- Assumption 4: States are abstract and used to model pre/post conditions
-- Assumption 5: NFRs are modeled via proxy constraints on channel count and sharing
-- Open issue 1: NFR facts (performance, availability, scalability, usability) may conflict; e.g., #op.channel <=2 and >=2 force exactly 2 channels per operation, which may be too restrictive
-- Open issue 2: Edge case assertions (ec_safe_1, ec_safe_2, ec_safe_3, ec_safe_4) may be too strong or not aligned with actual requirements; they are kept as-is for verification
-- Open issue 3: The model does not include explicit time or scheduling logic; overlapping and gaps are abstracted via resource sharing and state differences


